1
00:00:10,980 --> 00:00:12,660
(Division Four)

2
00:00:12,660 --> 00:00:14,320
(Division Four Chief's Office)

3
00:00:14,320 --> 00:00:15,190
Chief Yuan,

4
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:17,870
none of the other divisions
will take this case.

5
00:00:18,070 --> 00:00:20,070
(Case Report Log)
This is a hot potato.

6
00:00:20,070 --> 00:00:22,510
They're obviously dumping it on us.

7
00:00:22,870 --> 00:00:24,640
You can't take this case.

8
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:25,760
Yang Dezhi,

9
00:00:26,240 --> 00:00:27,640
what's a policeman supposed to do?

10
00:00:27,640 --> 00:00:29,350
Protect the innocent,
and keep the peace.

11
00:00:29,360 --> 00:00:31,350
Citizens file reports,
but the police pass the buck.

12
00:00:31,360 --> 00:00:32,470
"Keeping the peace", huh?

13
00:00:32,480 --> 00:00:34,560
=Cases Between Us=
No, you can't put it that way.

14
00:00:34,560 --> 00:00:35,424
Director Wu

15
00:00:35,440 --> 00:00:36,720
=Episode 2=
is a senior official

16
00:00:36,780 --> 00:00:38,800
at the Internal Affairs Department.
One of his maids

17
00:00:38,816 --> 00:00:40,200
fell into a well and died.

18
00:00:40,470 --> 00:00:42,150
That's not a public safety issue.

19
00:00:42,150 --> 00:00:43,750
It's a family matter.

20
00:00:44,390 --> 00:00:44,960
A few days ago,

21
00:00:45,240 --> 00:00:46,670
Director Wu's concubine

22
00:00:46,670 --> 00:00:48,350
died in childbirth at the hospital.

23
00:00:49,320 --> 00:00:51,470
The way she died was terrifying.

24
00:00:51,470 --> 00:00:53,390
I heard it was haunted.

25
00:00:53,600 --> 00:00:54,240
Haunted?

26
00:00:54,750 --> 00:00:55,710
It's true.

27
00:00:55,710 --> 00:00:57,520
Everyone at the hospital saw it.

28
00:00:57,520 --> 00:00:59,470
Director Wu was scared out of his wits.

29
00:00:59,470 --> 00:01:00,600
He was possessed.

30
00:01:00,600 --> 00:01:01,430
He kept

31
00:01:01,430 --> 00:01:02,390
rambling nonsense.

32
00:01:02,390 --> 00:01:03,430
The rumors are still

33
00:01:03,430 --> 00:01:04,640
all over town.

34
00:01:04,640 --> 00:01:06,040
What does any of that

35
00:01:06,040 --> 00:01:07,040
have to do with this case?

36
00:01:07,760 --> 00:01:09,430
The maid who fell into the well

37
00:01:09,430 --> 00:01:11,870
was the concubine's handmaid.

38
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:12,840
I heard

39
00:01:13,040 --> 00:01:14,870
Director Wu's wife
couldn't have children,

40
00:01:14,950 --> 00:01:16,480
so he took a concubine.

41
00:01:16,710 --> 00:01:18,230
Now both mother and child are dead.

42
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:19,710
Then the handmaid

43
00:01:19,710 --> 00:01:20,790
dies in a well, too.

44
00:01:20,790 --> 00:01:23,280
Don't you think something's fishy?

45
00:01:23,870 --> 00:01:25,120
Who's Director Wu's wife?

46
00:01:25,350 --> 00:01:26,790
Young Lady Zhao.

47
00:01:27,950 --> 00:01:28,680
Which Zhao family?

48
00:01:29,040 --> 00:01:30,710
How many Zhao families are there
in Beijing?

49
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:33,350
Minister Zhao Chengru of Education.

50
00:01:38,790 --> 00:01:39,510
Young Master.

51
00:01:39,936 --> 00:01:42,352
(Gu Xishan's Household Registry File)
Who exactly was Gu Xishan?

52
00:01:42,480 --> 00:01:43,480
He was a Chinese physician

53
00:01:43,480 --> 00:01:44,720
who practiced near Chongwen Gate.

54
00:01:44,730 --> 00:01:46,490
Two years ago,
a patient died under his care.

55
00:01:46,500 --> 00:01:47,970
(Investigation Report)
He was convicted of manslaughter.

56
00:01:47,980 --> 00:01:49,408
He killed himself in prison last year.

57
00:01:50,480 --> 00:01:51,480
He's dead?

58
00:01:51,870 --> 00:01:53,950
Then it's his ghost coming back?

59
00:01:54,280 --> 00:01:55,510
Ghosts?

60
00:01:55,920 --> 00:01:56,950
You actually believe that?

61
00:01:58,704 --> 00:01:59,790
Let's go to Gu's Clinic

62
00:02:00,120 --> 00:02:01,000
at Chongwen Gate.

63
00:02:01,060 --> 00:02:03,380
(Gu's Clinic)

64
00:02:05,310 --> 00:02:06,510
Old geezer,

65
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:08,280
trying to put me in check?

66
00:02:08,580 --> 00:02:09,940
(Gu's Clinic)
Eat it.

67
00:02:10,030 --> 00:02:10,710
Try me.

68
00:02:10,910 --> 00:02:12,240
Have a death wish?

69
00:02:12,272 --> 00:02:12,840
Eat your piece.

70
00:02:20,412 --> 00:02:22,310
I'm going to kick you.

71
00:02:22,960 --> 00:02:23,680
Mister,

72
00:02:24,030 --> 00:02:25,000
excuse me.

73
00:02:25,310 --> 00:02:26,400
Is this Gu's Clinic?

74
00:02:26,624 --> 00:02:27,560
You mean Physician Gu?

75
00:02:27,664 --> 00:02:28,960
Why are you looking for them?

76
00:02:29,430 --> 00:02:30,400
Is anyone from the family

77
00:02:30,400 --> 00:02:31,680
still around?

78
00:02:31,680 --> 00:02:33,080
No one's left.

79
00:02:33,080 --> 00:02:34,360
After Physician Gu died,

80
00:02:34,360 --> 00:02:35,560
his wife took her own life too.

81
00:02:35,680 --> 00:02:36,960
And her daughter disappeared

82
00:02:36,960 --> 00:02:38,400
not long after.

83
00:02:41,030 --> 00:02:42,310
Do you remember

84
00:02:42,310 --> 00:02:43,190
what she looked like?

85
00:02:43,680 --> 00:02:44,190
Sure.

86
00:02:45,150 --> 00:02:46,030
Willow brows.

87
00:02:46,030 --> 00:02:46,840
A cherry mouth.

88
00:02:47,240 --> 00:02:47,840
Straight bangs.

89
00:02:47,840 --> 00:02:48,190
Right.

90
00:02:48,190 --> 00:02:48,960
Straight bangs.

91
00:02:49,840 --> 00:02:50,470
Young Master.

92
00:02:53,280 --> 00:02:54,630
What exactly is that?

93
00:02:54,630 --> 00:02:55,280
Willow brows.

94
00:02:55,280 --> 00:02:56,030
A cherry mouth.

95
00:02:56,520 --> 00:02:57,080
Straight bangs?

96
00:02:57,080 --> 00:02:57,430
Yes.

97
00:02:57,430 --> 00:02:58,520
Straight bangs.

98
00:02:59,150 --> 00:03:00,840
Could you describe her one more time?

99
00:03:01,630 --> 00:03:02,520
Willow brows.

100
00:03:02,800 --> 00:03:03,800
A cherry mouth.

101
00:03:03,800 --> 00:03:04,520
Straight bangs.

102
00:03:05,190 --> 00:03:06,240
Are you a cat?

103
00:03:06,240 --> 00:03:07,240
You didn't make a sound.

104
00:03:21,056 --> 00:03:22,470
I must say, it looks just like her.

105
00:03:22,470 --> 00:03:23,910
It looks just like Xiumei.

106
00:03:24,190 --> 00:03:24,870
It's Xiumei.

107
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:32,710
You know her?

108
00:03:34,400 --> 00:03:35,240
No.

109
00:03:35,240 --> 00:03:35,960
Really?

110
00:03:36,360 --> 00:03:37,030
Really don't.

111
00:03:40,430 --> 00:03:41,240
Chief Yuan,

112
00:03:42,080 --> 00:03:43,800
what brings you here?

113
00:03:44,464 --> 00:03:46,000
I was on official business this morning.

114
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:46,912
My mind was elsewhere,

115
00:03:46,928 --> 00:03:47,910
so I was rude to you.

116
00:03:47,910 --> 00:03:49,910
I've come to apologize.

117
00:03:52,150 --> 00:03:53,280
Now you know me?

118
00:03:54,400 --> 00:03:56,000
I'd like to treat you to a meal.

119
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:57,150
Would you do me the honor?

120
00:03:57,360 --> 00:03:58,870
You came all this way to buy me lunch?

121
00:03:58,870 --> 00:03:59,520
That's right.

122
00:03:59,800 --> 00:04:00,240
Fine.

123
00:04:00,624 --> 00:04:02,176
Let's go to Tiansheng Restaurant.

124
00:04:02,208 --> 00:04:03,840
I'll tell them to braise
the bear's paw.

125
00:04:16,040 --> 00:04:16,920
You don't like noodles?

126
00:04:17,240 --> 00:04:18,560
The fried bean sauce is too watery,

127
00:04:18,560 --> 00:04:19,888
and there aren't enough toppings.

128
00:04:20,430 --> 00:04:21,680
You're not picky at all.

129
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:24,040
I'm just a copper.

130
00:04:24,360 --> 00:04:25,510
I'm lucky if I get a full meal.

131
00:04:25,510 --> 00:04:26,600
I can't afford to be picky.

132
00:04:27,430 --> 00:04:28,070
Chief Yuan,

133
00:04:28,510 --> 00:04:30,040
do you really think I'm a fool?

134
00:04:30,800 --> 00:04:31,750
You studied abroad.

135
00:04:32,390 --> 00:04:33,070
In Britain.

136
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:35,040
At a military academy.

137
00:04:35,750 --> 00:04:36,750
That's not something

138
00:04:36,750 --> 00:04:38,080
an ordinary family could afford.

139
00:04:39,248 --> 00:04:40,120
You looked into me?

140
00:04:42,120 --> 00:04:43,000
Your leather shoes.

141
00:04:43,160 --> 00:04:44,430
Grenson from London.

142
00:04:45,270 --> 00:04:46,750
They don't sell ready-made pairs.

143
00:04:46,750 --> 00:04:47,510
Only custom orders.

144
00:04:48,190 --> 00:04:49,720
Your right deltoid,

145
00:04:50,040 --> 00:04:51,510
levator scapulae, and trapezius

146
00:04:51,600 --> 00:04:53,070
are all more developed than your left.

147
00:04:53,800 --> 00:04:55,040
That's from years

148
00:04:55,040 --> 00:04:56,390
of intensive

149
00:04:56,390 --> 00:04:57,190
firearms training.

150
00:04:57,720 --> 00:04:58,950
If I'm not mistaken,

151
00:04:58,950 --> 00:05:00,870
that enamel badge on your chest

152
00:05:00,870 --> 00:05:03,408
is from the British Artillery
and Engineering Military Academy.

153
00:05:03,800 --> 00:05:05,830
And that sketch you made earlier,

154
00:05:05,830 --> 00:05:07,390
you learned that there, too.

155
00:05:07,720 --> 00:05:08,360
Yes.

156
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:09,870
It was an elective.

157
00:05:10,270 --> 00:05:11,920
Criminal portrait sketching.

158
00:05:17,870 --> 00:05:18,600
Young Master Zhao,

159
00:05:19,090 --> 00:05:20,270
I'll be straight with you.

160
00:05:20,510 --> 00:05:21,950
I'm here to ask you a favor.

161
00:05:22,390 --> 00:05:23,950
The case I'm working on

162
00:05:23,950 --> 00:05:24,848
involves the Wu family.

163
00:05:25,104 --> 00:05:26,240
I'd like to meet your sister.

164
00:05:26,700 --> 00:05:28,750
That explains it.
First, you pretended not to know me,

165
00:05:28,750 --> 00:05:30,040
and now you're cozying up to me.

166
00:05:30,870 --> 00:05:32,190
So you just want to use me.

167
00:05:32,656 --> 00:05:33,830
That's a separate matter.

168
00:05:34,256 --> 00:05:35,632
If I hadn't stepped in this morning,

169
00:05:35,664 --> 00:05:37,000
you wouldn't be in one piece now.

170
00:05:39,830 --> 00:05:40,750
Why should I help you?

171
00:05:40,928 --> 00:05:43,520
You're investigating Wu Shichuan
because of your sister, aren't you?

172
00:05:43,950 --> 00:05:45,120
Your father is Zhao Chengru,

173
00:05:45,360 --> 00:05:46,510
Wu Shichuan's father-in-law.

174
00:05:46,830 --> 00:05:47,950
If something happens to him,

175
00:05:48,430 --> 00:05:50,750
your father will be
under a lot of public pressure.

176
00:05:56,288 --> 00:05:57,510
My sister has quite a temper.

177
00:05:57,510 --> 00:05:59,104
You're worried
she'll let something slip?

178
00:06:00,830 --> 00:06:01,950
I'm worried she'll hit you.

179
00:06:01,950 --> 00:06:03,216
If she slaps me on the left cheek,

180
00:06:03,264 --> 00:06:04,656
I'll gladly offer her the right.

181
00:06:05,480 --> 00:06:07,560
I was properly trained in Britain

182
00:06:07,560 --> 00:06:08,630
to be a gentleman.

183
00:06:12,496 --> 00:06:14,304
How long has your sister been married?

184
00:06:14,720 --> 00:06:15,510
Over five years.

185
00:06:15,640 --> 00:06:17,744
Did she marry for love,
or was it an arranged marriage?

186
00:06:17,790 --> 00:06:19,296
Arranged. Both families are Bannermen.

187
00:06:19,328 --> 00:06:21,030
Our families have been close
for generations.

188
00:06:21,040 --> 00:06:22,370
They're childhood friends.

189
00:06:22,384 --> 00:06:23,360
Do they get along?

190
00:06:23,510 --> 00:06:24,430
Do they argue much?

191
00:06:24,430 --> 00:06:25,120
Once in a while.

192
00:06:25,130 --> 00:06:26,590
If they do,
she'll come to our parents' house.

193
00:06:26,608 --> 00:06:27,830
He'll talk her into coming back.

194
00:06:27,840 --> 00:06:28,928
What do they fight about?

195
00:06:30,680 --> 00:06:31,630
Why do you want to know?

196
00:06:33,560 --> 00:06:34,160
Just curious.

197
00:06:35,800 --> 00:06:37,070
Curiosity kills cats.

198
00:06:38,448 --> 00:06:40,360
You should be grateful
that wasn't a baseball.

199
00:06:42,510 --> 00:06:43,480
Who is this?

200
00:06:43,510 --> 00:06:45,760
I'm Yuan Hong,
Jingshi Police Department Division Four.

201
00:06:46,430 --> 00:06:47,360
I'm here

202
00:06:47,360 --> 00:06:48,720
to ask about

203
00:06:49,040 --> 00:06:50,160
your husband's concubine.

204
00:06:50,680 --> 00:06:51,920
Why are you asking about her?

205
00:06:52,190 --> 00:06:53,480
We've received a murder report.

206
00:06:53,680 --> 00:06:55,240
The victim was her maid.

207
00:06:55,480 --> 00:06:56,310
Cui Xi is dead?

208
00:06:56,680 --> 00:06:57,480
How did she die?

209
00:06:57,680 --> 00:06:58,630
She fell into a well.

210
00:06:58,816 --> 00:06:59,870
The Wu family reported it?

211
00:07:00,950 --> 00:07:02,480
The Wu family is arranging the funeral.

212
00:07:02,496 --> 00:07:04,000
It was the maid's family who did it.

213
00:07:05,360 --> 00:07:06,040
Well, well.

214
00:07:06,390 --> 00:07:07,270
Just as I thought.

215
00:07:07,360 --> 00:07:08,160
To that family,

216
00:07:08,160 --> 00:07:09,630
a maid's life was never worth much.

217
00:07:10,896 --> 00:07:12,120
What do you want to ask me?

218
00:07:24,600 --> 00:07:25,510
How did the concubine

219
00:07:25,510 --> 00:07:26,920
come into your household?

220
00:07:26,930 --> 00:07:28,960
I couldn't get pregnant
after five years of marriage.

221
00:07:28,976 --> 00:07:30,870
The Wu family line couldn't end with me.

222
00:07:30,910 --> 00:07:32,720
Taking a concubine
was only a matter of time.

223
00:07:32,800 --> 00:07:34,680
How was your relationship with her?

224
00:07:34,680 --> 00:07:35,160
Hey.

225
00:07:35,480 --> 00:07:36,680
Is this an interrogation?

226
00:07:38,190 --> 00:07:38,920
Just curious.

227
00:07:38,960 --> 00:07:40,510
It's only natural for you to suspect me.

228
00:07:40,510 --> 00:07:42,768
But Qing Miao joining the family
was a good thing for me.

229
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:45,600
At least someone could share the burden.

230
00:07:45,830 --> 00:07:47,390
Not long after she got pregnant,

231
00:07:47,390 --> 00:07:48,510
I went to Shanghai.

232
00:07:48,510 --> 00:07:50,530
I didn't come back
until she was about to give birth.

233
00:07:50,544 --> 00:07:51,430
As for Cui Xi,

234
00:07:52,064 --> 00:07:54,360
the Old Madam assigned her
to Qing Miao after she moved in.

235
00:07:54,830 --> 00:07:55,720
If you don't believe me,

236
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:57,040
you're welcome to check.

237
00:07:58,000 --> 00:07:58,510
I do.

238
00:07:59,360 --> 00:08:00,688
Thank you for your cooperation.

239
00:08:05,310 --> 00:08:05,870
By the way,

240
00:08:07,600 --> 00:08:09,390
could I have a photo of Qing Miao?

241
00:08:10,040 --> 00:08:10,630
No.

242
00:08:14,630 --> 00:08:15,800
What I mean is,

243
00:08:17,480 --> 00:08:18,560
we don't exactly

244
00:08:18,560 --> 00:08:20,120
have one now.

245
00:08:20,750 --> 00:08:21,830
My sister is Wu Shichuan's

246
00:08:21,830 --> 00:08:22,870
lawfully wedded wife.

247
00:08:22,870 --> 00:08:24,000
Why would she be keeping

248
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:25,630
a photo of the concubine? Right, Wan'er?

249
00:08:28,830 --> 00:08:29,430
Go get it.

250
00:08:37,270 --> 00:08:37,720
Here.

251
00:08:37,720 --> 00:08:38,320
Thank you.

252
00:08:41,270 --> 00:08:42,720
Xiumei was the concubine Qing Miao.

253
00:08:42,784 --> 00:08:43,960
Why didn't you tell me sooner?

254
00:08:49,580 --> 00:08:53,700
(Changsheng Tennis Club)

255
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:55,600
Chief Yuan,

256
00:08:55,840 --> 00:08:57,030
what are you investigating?

257
00:08:57,030 --> 00:08:58,200
Just the maid's death?

258
00:08:59,440 --> 00:09:00,150
Official business.

259
00:09:00,150 --> 00:09:01,232
I'm not at liberty to say.

260
00:09:01,600 --> 00:09:02,720
So you're going to ditch me

261
00:09:02,720 --> 00:09:03,750
after using me?

262
00:09:03,850 --> 00:09:05,760
Whatever gave you that idea,
Young Master Zhao?

263
00:09:05,824 --> 00:09:06,736
Speaking of which,

264
00:09:06,768 --> 00:09:08,352
weren't you the one
who lied to me first?

265
00:09:09,390 --> 00:09:11,480
You've always lied.

266
00:09:13,630 --> 00:09:15,000
What do you mean by always?

267
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:16,000
Who else have I lied to?

268
00:09:19,080 --> 00:09:20,600
That wasn't lying.

269
00:09:20,600 --> 00:09:21,472
Then what was it?

270
00:09:21,870 --> 00:09:22,870
Think about it.

271
00:09:23,200 --> 00:09:24,440
My brother-in-law's concubine

272
00:09:24,440 --> 00:09:26,080
was practically half a sister to me.

273
00:09:26,200 --> 00:09:27,344
Then she's my family.

274
00:09:27,360 --> 00:09:29,440
How could I tell you
my family's business so easily?

275
00:09:29,440 --> 00:09:31,200
I was testing you.

276
00:09:32,120 --> 00:09:33,550
So what are you getting at?

277
00:09:34,360 --> 00:09:37,080
We've been through this together now.

278
00:09:37,360 --> 00:09:38,416
That makes us friends.

279
00:09:38,420 --> 00:09:40,390
If you're investigating
something, take me with you.

280
00:09:40,390 --> 00:09:42,270
I can help you
with anything in this city.

281
00:09:42,750 --> 00:09:43,480
Young Master Zhao,

282
00:09:43,750 --> 00:09:44,390
drop the act.

283
00:09:44,480 --> 00:09:46,752
If you want to investigate
your brother-in-law, be my guest.

284
00:09:46,840 --> 00:09:47,320
Dezhi.

285
00:10:03,030 --> 00:10:03,750
Young Master,

286
00:10:04,480 --> 00:10:06,120
where are we going now?

287
00:10:07,960 --> 00:10:08,750
You're asking me?

288
00:10:10,440 --> 00:10:11,480
Who am I supposed to ask?

289
00:10:19,863 --> 00:10:22,823
(Jingshi Police Department)

290
00:10:31,630 --> 00:10:32,120
Hello?

291
00:10:34,510 --> 00:10:35,000
Hello?

292
00:11:24,840 --> 00:11:25,270
A ghost!

293
00:11:25,630 --> 00:11:26,600
It's a ghost!

294
00:11:26,600 --> 00:11:28,660
(Jingshi Police Department)

295
00:11:29,550 --> 00:11:30,910
(To the police who do nothing.)

296
00:11:31,120 --> 00:11:33,320
(To this day, words are useless.)

297
00:11:33,510 --> 00:11:34,480
(Justice is gone.)

298
00:11:34,480 --> 00:11:35,696
(My name can never be cleared.)

299
00:11:35,750 --> 00:11:37,760
(Today, I lay this curse
upon those who wronged me)

300
00:11:37,870 --> 00:11:39,000
(to vent my rage)

301
00:11:39,080 --> 00:11:40,384
(and bring peace to my soul.)

302
00:11:40,440 --> 00:11:41,630
(Written by Gu Xishan.)

303
00:11:43,270 --> 00:11:43,840
Report!

304
00:11:45,200 --> 00:11:47,960
Cui Xi's autopsy report is out.

305
00:11:48,120 --> 00:11:49,000
Please review it.

306
00:11:50,390 --> 00:11:51,550
Chronic arsenic poisoning.

307
00:11:51,552 --> 00:11:53,430
She had been taking it
for at least three months.

308
00:11:53,440 --> 00:11:55,270
When the poison took effect,
she became dizzy.

309
00:11:55,270 --> 00:11:57,328
(Forensic Report)
That's how she fell into the well.

310
00:11:57,392 --> 00:12:00,030
We found a box
of Longevity Pills at her home.

311
00:12:00,030 --> 00:12:01,790
They tested positive for arsenic.

312
00:12:02,030 --> 00:12:03,480
The other maids said

313
00:12:03,480 --> 00:12:04,910
the concubine gave them to her

314
00:12:04,910 --> 00:12:06,720
when she first became pregnant.

315
00:12:07,240 --> 00:12:09,910
Cui Xi took them every day
as a health tonic.

316
00:12:11,200 --> 00:12:13,270
The case is basically clear.

317
00:12:13,600 --> 00:12:15,360
The concubine poisoned her.

318
00:12:15,910 --> 00:12:17,440
Anyway, she's already dead.

319
00:12:18,270 --> 00:12:20,630
I'd say we can close the case.

320
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:28,600
Chief?

321
00:12:33,212 --> 00:12:34,840
Qing Miao had no grudges against Cui Xi.

322
00:12:35,264 --> 00:12:36,320
Why would she kill her?

323
00:12:36,720 --> 00:12:37,390
Uh...

324
00:12:43,856 --> 00:12:45,750
Is this how you normally wear
your uniform?

325
00:13:01,600 --> 00:13:03,120
A ghost!

326
00:13:03,420 --> 00:13:04,300
(Division Four)

327
00:13:15,960 --> 00:13:17,200
It's you, Young Master Zhao.

328
00:13:18,352 --> 00:13:20,000
It was you playing ghost last night.

329
00:13:20,360 --> 00:13:21,480
Am I out of my mind?

330
00:13:21,552 --> 00:13:23,984
Why would I pretend to be a ghost
and then turn myself in?

331
00:13:24,640 --> 00:13:25,952
It was a bunch of beggar kids.

332
00:13:25,960 --> 00:13:26,670
Where are they?

333
00:13:27,296 --> 00:13:28,980
Someone hired them.

334
00:13:28,992 --> 00:13:31,000
They're only trying
to make a living. I let them go.

335
00:13:31,270 --> 00:13:32,550
How could you let them go?

336
00:13:34,630 --> 00:13:36,150
Do you know who hired them?

337
00:13:37,440 --> 00:13:38,000
Qing Miao.

338
00:13:39,670 --> 00:13:40,550
Smart.

339
00:13:42,480 --> 00:13:43,440
How did you find out?

340
00:13:43,790 --> 00:13:46,000
There's nothing
in this city I can't dig up.

341
00:13:46,240 --> 00:13:47,750
Regretting not working with me now?

342
00:13:48,150 --> 00:13:49,270
I'll give you one more chance.

343
00:13:51,600 --> 00:13:53,630
You really don't know a good thing
when you see it.

344
00:13:56,120 --> 00:13:56,790
Coming in or not?

345
00:13:57,790 --> 00:13:58,440
Coming.

346
00:14:03,120 --> 00:14:03,960
Can't believe it.

347
00:14:05,120 --> 00:14:05,630
Really can't.

348
00:14:06,550 --> 00:14:07,360
Open the coffin?

349
00:14:07,568 --> 00:14:09,510
Absolutely not!
There are rules in our trade.

350
00:14:09,510 --> 00:14:10,960
Have you heard of the coffin curse?

351
00:14:10,960 --> 00:14:12,390
Anyone in the antiques business knows

352
00:14:12,390 --> 00:14:13,750
you never open a coffin

353
00:14:13,750 --> 00:14:14,550
or disturb a grave.

354
00:14:14,550 --> 00:14:16,150
Best case, you'll be haunted by bad luck

355
00:14:16,150 --> 00:14:16,960
and fall gravely ill.

356
00:14:16,960 --> 00:14:18,890
Worst case, you'll end up
dying a terrible death.

357
00:14:18,900 --> 00:14:20,360
This is asking for trouble.

358
00:14:26,270 --> 00:14:26,840
Fine.

359
00:14:27,680 --> 00:14:28,750
Then you can head home.

360
00:14:28,750 --> 00:14:29,360
You...

361
00:14:30,960 --> 00:14:32,832
You change your tune on a dime!

362
00:14:32,848 --> 00:14:33,888
You're investigating a case.

363
00:14:33,920 --> 00:14:35,910
Why do you have
to open the coffin? She's dead.

364
00:14:35,910 --> 00:14:37,270
Can't you let her rest in peace?

365
00:14:39,320 --> 00:14:40,440
Are you sure she's dead?

366
00:14:47,150 --> 00:14:48,910
Back then, Gu Xishan's patient died.

367
00:14:48,992 --> 00:14:50,330
(Ta Kung Pao Newspaper)
Reporters discovered his ancestors

368
00:14:50,340 --> 00:14:51,648
were shamans from western Hunan.

369
00:14:51,870 --> 00:14:53,290
(Gu's Clinic)
The deceased

370
00:14:53,300 --> 00:14:54,390
had argued with him before,

371
00:14:54,390 --> 00:14:56,390
so they suspected
he'd poisoned the patient.

372
00:14:56,448 --> 00:14:57,760
Your brother-in-law, Wu Shichuan,

373
00:14:57,792 --> 00:14:59,640
(Jingshi High Court)
represented the Health Bureau

374
00:14:59,650 --> 00:15:00,590
and submitted the report.

375
00:15:00,600 --> 00:15:03,150
Gu Xishan was convicted
of negligent homicide

376
00:15:03,150 --> 00:15:04,272
and sentenced to three years.

377
00:15:04,720 --> 00:15:05,600
Last May,

378
00:15:05,910 --> 00:15:07,600
the Supreme Court upheld the verdict.

379
00:15:08,016 --> 00:15:08,790
That very night,

380
00:15:09,480 --> 00:15:11,120
Gu Xishan killed himself in prison.

381
00:15:12,270 --> 00:15:13,240
Not long after,

382
00:15:14,480 --> 00:15:16,600
Qing Miao married your brother-in-law.

383
00:15:18,550 --> 00:15:22,120
You think Wu Shichuan's incident,

384
00:15:22,360 --> 00:15:23,360
the maid's death,

385
00:15:23,888 --> 00:15:26,288
and the letter demanding justice
were all Qing Miao's doing?

386
00:15:28,150 --> 00:15:29,440
She may not be dead.

387
00:15:54,480 --> 00:15:56,270
How many guilty consciences
are you carrying?

388
00:15:56,270 --> 00:15:57,200
Why are you so scared?

389
00:15:59,030 --> 00:16:00,080
Who's scared?

390
00:16:00,360 --> 00:16:01,080
I'm cold.

391
00:16:01,080 --> 00:16:02,000
Block the wind for me.

392
00:16:02,030 --> 00:16:02,870
Young Master Zhao,

393
00:16:03,480 --> 00:16:05,360
why don't you wait in the car?

394
00:16:06,360 --> 00:16:07,960
I said I'm cold!

395
00:16:09,750 --> 00:16:11,390
Stop staring.

396
00:16:11,630 --> 00:16:12,390
We found the coffin!

397
00:16:24,150 --> 00:16:25,360
It's Qing Miao.

398
00:16:28,260 --> 00:16:31,660
(Peking Union Medical College)

399
00:16:34,600 --> 00:16:36,120
I'm not here to collect a debt.

400
00:16:40,390 --> 00:16:41,790
I've brought you a job.

401
00:16:44,550 --> 00:16:45,200
What kind of job?

402
00:16:48,390 --> 00:16:49,510
One that pays.

403
00:16:50,020 --> 00:16:52,500
(Du Wenjiu, Cardiac Surgeon,
Peking Union Medical College)

404
00:16:55,030 --> 00:16:56,200
You want me to examine a body?

405
00:16:57,750 --> 00:16:58,670
Where's your coroner?

406
00:16:58,832 --> 00:17:00,608
The coroner isn't good enough.
You'll do it.

407
00:17:02,912 --> 00:17:04,070
I'm not good enough either.

408
00:17:04,510 --> 00:17:05,110
Goodbye.

409
00:17:05,510 --> 00:17:06,400
Two silver coins.

410
00:17:14,304 --> 00:17:15,590
How do you two know each other?

411
00:17:16,160 --> 00:17:17,960
We met at the
British Embassy Christmas party.

412
00:17:18,400 --> 00:17:19,720
He broke one of my cups.

413
00:17:19,776 --> 00:17:21,200
He needs years to pay that off.

414
00:17:22,160 --> 00:17:23,550
What kind of cup costs that much?

415
00:17:24,120 --> 00:17:26,210
A Ming Dynasty Doucai Chicken Cup.
It isn't worth much.

416
00:17:26,224 --> 00:17:27,510
But he'll pay it off for years.

417
00:17:27,680 --> 00:17:29,000
Have some decency, will you?

418
00:17:29,440 --> 00:17:30,480
Do your job.

419
00:17:30,784 --> 00:17:31,750
Something's not right.

420
00:17:32,350 --> 00:17:33,920
You said she died in childbirth,

421
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:35,640
but there was no baby in her womb.

422
00:17:37,200 --> 00:17:38,160
What's going on?

423
00:17:38,680 --> 00:17:39,830
No baby?

424
00:17:41,030 --> 00:17:42,480
Then why was her belly so big?

425
00:17:42,720 --> 00:17:43,440
Cirrhosis.

426
00:17:43,680 --> 00:17:45,350
Her abdominal cavity was full of fluid.

427
00:17:45,408 --> 00:17:47,070
She was already in the terminal stage.

428
00:17:47,216 --> 00:17:48,480
Even if she hadn't been killed,

429
00:17:48,528 --> 00:17:50,384
she would've had
at most another month to live.

430
00:17:52,030 --> 00:17:53,070
Then how did no one realize

431
00:17:53,070 --> 00:17:54,912
she'd been faking the pregnancy
for over a year?

432
00:17:55,160 --> 00:17:56,830
She'd had a uterine curettage before.

433
00:17:56,830 --> 00:17:58,130
Her uterine lining was very thin.

434
00:17:58,270 --> 00:17:59,550
She probably stopped her periods

435
00:17:59,960 --> 00:18:01,640
to make everyone think she was pregnant.

436
00:18:01,744 --> 00:18:02,720
Enough with the details.

437
00:18:02,720 --> 00:18:04,110
What did she die of?

438
00:18:04,110 --> 00:18:05,640
She's been dead too long. I can't tell.

439
00:18:05,920 --> 00:18:07,200
Are you even a doctor?

440
00:18:08,590 --> 00:18:10,000
I'm a cardiac surgeon,

441
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:11,350
not a coroner.

442
00:18:11,350 --> 00:18:12,590
I've told you that many times.

443
00:18:16,384 --> 00:18:18,128
This earring hook has been sharpened.

444
00:18:18,960 --> 00:18:20,510
Normal earring hooks have rounded tips

445
00:18:20,510 --> 00:18:21,480
so they don't hurt people.

446
00:18:22,448 --> 00:18:24,240
This one was
deliberately filed to a point.

447
00:18:24,960 --> 00:18:25,350
Torch.

448
00:18:37,680 --> 00:18:39,510
The killer most likely used this hook

449
00:18:39,510 --> 00:18:40,480
to pierce her eardrum.

450
00:18:41,160 --> 00:18:42,480
It was murder?

451
00:18:42,830 --> 00:18:43,640
An adult ear canal

452
00:18:43,640 --> 00:18:45,168
is usually 2.5 to 3.5 centimeters deep.

453
00:18:45,808 --> 00:18:47,110
This hook is four centimeters long.

454
00:18:47,152 --> 00:18:48,240
It pierced the eardrum,

455
00:18:48,240 --> 00:18:49,520
and went straight into the brain,

456
00:18:49,630 --> 00:18:51,310
causing blood to seep into the brain.

457
00:18:51,312 --> 00:18:52,320
It killed her instantly.

458
00:18:52,830 --> 00:18:54,590
The wound was tiny.

459
00:18:54,590 --> 00:18:56,080
There was very little external bleeding,

460
00:18:56,310 --> 00:18:57,310
so no one noticed.

461
00:18:58,440 --> 00:18:59,240
That means

462
00:19:00,110 --> 00:19:01,830
the killer was in the delivery room.

463
00:19:03,360 --> 00:19:04,590
- The doctor.
- The doctor.

464
00:19:05,312 --> 00:19:07,920
(End of Episode 2)

465
00:19:09,520 --> 00:19:11,160
♪Side by side,
we journey through this life♪

466
00:19:11,160 --> 00:19:12,700
♪Troubled times
are but a laughing matter♪

467
00:19:12,700 --> 00:19:13,950
♪However, the world changes♪

468
00:19:13,950 --> 00:19:15,870
♪You'll still be by my side♪

469
00:19:15,870 --> 00:19:17,560
♪Side by side,
we journey through this life♪

470
00:19:17,560 --> 00:19:19,130
♪Praise and blame come and go♪

471
00:19:19,130 --> 00:19:20,700
♪If this is my final chapter♪

472
00:19:20,700 --> 00:19:23,200
♪I'll solve this mystery with you♪
